Definition: perplexed by many conflicting situations or statements
Example: filled with bewilderment; obviously bemused by his questions; bewildered and confused; a cloudy and confounded philosopher; just a mixed-up kid; she felt lost on the first day of school
Synonyms: befuddled, bemused, bewildered, confounded, confused, noun, cognition, confusedness, lost, mazed, mixed-up, at_sea, perplexed, by, many, conflicting, situations, or, statements, filled, with, bewilderment, obviously, his, questions, and, a, cloudy, philosopher, just, kid, she, felt, on, the, first, day, of, school
Category: adj.all
